Privacy Policy
Introduction
Welcome to Autism BASICS ("the App"). This Privacy Policy is designed to help you understand how we collect, use, disclose, and safeguard the personal information of children who use our App. We are committed to protecting the privacy and safety of all users, especially children. Please read this Privacy Policy carefully to ensure you understand our practices.
Purchases of Home Therapy Resources
Our website, accessible at
Wellness Hub Home Therapy Resources
, offers a range of downloadable resources for home therapy, such as Autism and Speech therapies, which include products like Actions Flashcards for Kids. Please note:
Non-Refundable:
All purchases made through our website are final and non-refundable once completed. We encourage you to review your selection carefully before purchasing.
Download and Usage:
Upon completion of a purchase, resources will be available for download through the user account. The usage of these resources is subject to the terms outlined in this Privacy Policy and our Terms of Service.
Information We Collect
User Information:
We collect limited personal information during the registration process, such as username and email.
We may collect information about the child's progress and performance within the App to provide a better learning experience.
Device Information:
We may automatically collect information about the device, such as the device type, operating system, and unique device identifiers.
Usage Information:
We collect information about how the child interacts with the App, including which activities they use, the time spent on the App, and any errors or crashes
Audio Data:
The App records audio data during usage of the Speech Recognition feature to help gauge a child's pronunciation. This audio data is used solely for the purpose of learning within the App and is not stored by us. Google processes these audio clips and does not store them or use them in any other way.
How We Use the Information
We use the information collected for the following purposes:
To Provide and Improve the App:
We use the information to provide, maintain, and improve the App, including personalizing the content and activities to suit the child's learning needs.
Communication:
We may use the email information to communicate for support feedback and to provide updates about the App.
Analytics:
We use the data for analytical purposes to understand how the App is used, identify areas for improvement, and make data-driven decisions to enhance the learning experience.
Disclosure of Information
We do not sell, rent, or trade children's personal information. We may disclose information as follows:
Service Providers:
We may share app analytics with trusted third-party service providers who assist us in operating and improving the App.
Legal Requirements:
We may disclose information in response to a legal obligation or to protect our rights, privacy, safety, or property.
Parental Consent
We require parental consent before making any in-app purchase or redirecting to a browser from the App. Parents or legal guardians have the right to review, delete, or request changes to their child's information.
Subscription
The App offers premium features that can be purchased for monthly, quarterly, or yearly periods. Access to these premium options is behind a parental lock so as to prevent any accidental purchase by the child. These purchases are not auto-renewed and need to be done again after one premium validity ends.
Security
We take reasonable measures to protect the information collected from unauthorized access, disclosure, alteration, or destruction.
Data Deletion
You can delete your account from the menu in the app after logging in. Once this option is selected, all the user data is deleted immediately. For further queries, please write to us at the provided email.
Contact Information
If you have any questions, concerns, or requests related to this Privacy Policy or the App, please contact us at:
Email:
care@mywellnesshub.in
Phone:
+91 888 1299 888
Changes to the Privacy Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy to reflect changes in our practices or legal requirements. We will notify you of any significant changes through the App or other appropriate means.
By using our App, you consent to the practices described in this Privacy Policy. Please ensure that you review and understand this Privacy Policy, especially if you allow your child to use our App.
Last updated: 29th December, 2023